</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDC1639492FFFD4FEB6FD48FAC5DC8D" blockId="8.[264,1323,284,950]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">
Remarks. The new species is quite similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C636DBA492FFFD4FCE6FD48FBC1DC2E" authorityName="Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[872,1055,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guizhouense">
<emphasis id="B917CA2B492FFFD4FCE6FD48FBC1DC2E" box="[872,1055,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. guizhouense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated from the latter by following characters: proboscis brown, arista nearly as long as head + thorax, 5 
<emphasis id="B917CA2B492FFFD4FEFFFCF9FEA0DC5E" bold="true" box="[369,382,845,869]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">–</emphasis>
6 long irregularly paired acr, ventral arm of male cercus without curved projection; in 
<taxonomicName id="4C636DBA492FFFD4FEEAFCC0FDC9DCB6" authorityName="Yang" authorityYear="1995" box="[356,535,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guizhouense">
<emphasis id="B917CA2B492FFFD4FEEAFCC0FDC9DCB6" box="[356,535,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">C. guizhouense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, proboscis black, arista much longer than head + thorax, 4 
<emphasis id="B917CA2B492FFFD4FB48FCC1FB0DDCB6" bold="true" box="[1222,1235,885,909]" pageId="8" pageNumber="55">–</emphasis>
5 irregularly paired acr, ventral arm of male cercus with strongly curved apico­inner projection.
</paragraph>
